stevejobs.name: Steve Jobs
stevejobs.description: Steve Jobs was an American business magnate, industrial designer, investor, and media proprietor. He was the chairman, chief executive officer (CEO), and co-founder of Apple Inc.

jeongjooyoung.name: Jeong Joo-Young
jeongjooyoung.description: Jeong Joo-young is a South Korean entrepreneur and the founder of Hyundai Group, making significant contributions to the economic development of South Korea.

brucelee.name: Bruce Lee
brucelee.description: Bruce Lee was a Chinese martial artist and actor, widely known as a global icon in Hong Kong cinema.

abrahamlincoln.name: Abraham Lincoln
abrahamlincoln.description: Abraham Lincoln was the 16th President of the United States, playing a crucial role during the American Civil War era in advocating for racial equality and the emancipation of slaves.

juliuscaesar.name: Julius Caesar
juliuscaesar.description: Julius Caesar was a Roman Emperor, renowned for his political prowess and conquests that significantly expanded the Roman Empire, leading it into its golden age.

cocochanel.name: Coco Chanel
cocochanel.description: Coco Chanel was a French fashion designer and businesswoman, founder of the Chanel brand, and a significant figure in 20th-century fashion.

waltdisney.name: Walt Disney
waltdisney.description: Walt Disney was an American entrepreneur, animator, and film producer, best known as the co-founder of The Walt Disney Company, and a pioneer of the American animation industry.

henryford.name: Henry Ford
henryford.description: Henry Ford was an American industrialist and the founder of the Ford Motor Company, revolutionizing the automobile industry with his assembly line production and making cars accessible to the masses.
